00:46:45.580 --> 00:46:50.610
So I get asked that question
a lot about children.

00:46:50.610 --> 00:46:54.430
You would deal with them in
terms of this subject in the

00:46:54.430 --> 00:46:59.310
same way you deal with them in
another potentially dangerous

00:46:59.310 --> 00:47:00.360
activities.

00:47:00.360 --> 00:47:04.160
Driving a car, you make sure
they have skills to do that.

00:47:04.160 --> 00:47:06.770
You make sure that they
understand under what

00:47:06.770 --> 00:47:10.340
conditions that should happen,
and how it should happen.

00:47:10.340 --> 00:47:12.840
Sexual behaviors.

00:47:12.840 --> 00:47:14.390
I'm sure you had sex at--

00:47:14.390 --> 00:47:15.400
I don't know when.

00:47:15.400 --> 00:47:16.650
That's a joke.

00:47:20.390 --> 00:47:23.670
But the point is is that that's
certainly a potentially

00:47:23.670 --> 00:47:27.780
dangerous activity, and we
manage to make sure that our

00:47:27.780 --> 00:47:29.320
kids stay safe.

00:47:29.320 --> 00:47:31.510
The same is true with drugs.

00:47:31.510 --> 00:47:34.330
Give them the appropriate
amount of education.

00:47:34.330 --> 00:47:39.370
They understand that if you use
some drugs before school,

00:47:39.370 --> 00:47:41.980
that's inconsistent with
the goals of this

00:47:41.980 --> 00:47:44.040
household, the family.

00:47:44.040 --> 00:47:49.190
And so, you just treat it just
like any other activity that

00:47:49.190 --> 00:47:52.800
might impact negatively
on their ability

00:47:52.800 --> 00:47:56.180
to do well in life.

00:47:56.180 --> 00:47:58.620
Thank you.

00:47:58.620 --> 00:48:00.640
AUDIENCE: So, I have a non-drug
question here.

00:48:00.640 --> 00:48:02.660
You mentioned in the first
section of your talk, while

00:48:02.660 --> 00:48:07.150
you were in England, that you
were able to sort of ground

00:48:07.150 --> 00:48:09.960
