00:51:18.070 --> 00:51:19.510
AUDIENCE: So, the first
question is,

00:51:19.510 --> 00:51:21.800
is there any evidence--

00:51:21.800 --> 00:51:22.810
CARL HART: Oh, personality.

00:51:22.810 --> 00:51:23.720
AUDIENCE: Just about
the personality.

00:51:23.720 --> 00:51:26.040
Because it does seem
to me, and I--

00:51:26.040 --> 00:51:26.430
CARL HART: Right on.

00:51:26.430 --> 00:51:26.980
I got you.

00:51:26.980 --> 00:51:29.980
AUDIENCE: I am totally a
proponent of drugs it is not a

00:51:29.980 --> 00:51:30.140
color thing.

00:51:30.140 --> 00:51:32.592
CARL HART: It's OK, we don't
have to do our personal

00:51:32.592 --> 00:51:33.670
divulging here, it's
all right.

00:51:33.670 --> 00:51:35.530
AUDIENCE: Oh no, no, I mean,
I'm just saying if someone

00:51:35.530 --> 00:51:39.890
says it effects one race or
one gender or whatever

00:51:39.890 --> 00:51:42.510
disproportionally to the other,
I completely disagree.

00:51:42.510 --> 00:51:43.870
I think it's a personality
thing.

00:51:43.870 --> 00:51:45.950
CARL HART: So a personality
thing.

00:51:45.950 --> 00:51:48.370
There is no evidence to support
the idea that somebody

00:51:48.370 --> 00:51:49.770
has an addictive personality.

00:51:49.770 --> 00:51:52.230
Although it works well in
terms of pop culture.

00:51:52.230 --> 00:51:54.230
But there's no evidence
to support that's.

00:51:54.230 --> 00:51:55.370
That's one.

00:51:55.370 --> 00:51:57.120
And you're right--

00:51:57.120 --> 00:52:01.220
drug addiction certainly
does not discriminate.

00:52:01.220 --> 00:52:02.770
That's the fact.

00:52:02.770 --> 00:52:07.270
But you're asking is there any
evidence for us to know what

00:52:07.270 --> 00:52:12.150
causes someone to become
addicted to drugs?

00:52:12.150 --> 00:52:14.850
A lot of science is looking
for the biological sort of

00:52:14.850 --> 00:52:17.580
explanation, as well
as it should.

00:52:17.580 --> 00:52:20.490
But I think that it's more
simple than that.

00:52:20.490 --> 00:52:26.720
If we look at the criteria
for addiction--

00:52:26.720 --> 00:52:33.310
inability to cut down your use
of the drug, using the drug in

00:52:33.310 --> 00:52:37.790
situations that are places you
in, potentially, harm's way,

00:52:37.790 --> 00:52:41.320
using the drug despite the fact
that you have knowledge

00:52:41.320 --> 00:52:46.100
that it causes you physical
or psychological problems.

00:52:46.100 --> 00:52:50.440
So, you go down the list of
these criteria, and these

00:52:50.440 --> 00:52:53.460
criteria mainly are sort
of behaviorally

00:52:53.460 --> 00:52:55.690
irresponsible people.

00:52:55.690 --> 00:53:01.020
And so, when you look at that
throughout, it tells you that

00:53:01.020 --> 00:53:04.020
even before the drug use,
folks may have been

00:53:04.020 --> 00:53:09.070
over-indulging or irresponsible
in some ways.

00:53:09.070 --> 00:53:12.100
Of course this isn't the case
for everyone, but I think

00:53:12.100 --> 00:53:13.830
that's a large component.

00:53:13.830 --> 00:53:21.180
And so I think that if we simply
look at the behaviors,

00:53:21.180 --> 00:53:23.580
help people to get better
skills, a wide range of

00:53:23.580 --> 00:53:25.150
things-- how to be more
responsible, a

00:53:25.150 --> 00:53:26.530
wide range of things.

00:53:26.530 --> 00:53:29.180
So I think that we
have overlooked

00:53:29.180 --> 00:53:30.970
those sort of factors.

00:53:30.970 --> 00:53:34.680
Now, back to your second
question, about what about in

00:53:34.680 --> 00:53:37.230
the communities where
people don't have

00:53:37.230 --> 00:53:39.440
rules, as you put it.

00:53:39.440 --> 00:53:44.800
Believe me, there are rules
in every social circle.

00:53:44.800 --> 00:53:46.030
There are rules.

00:53:46.030 --> 00:53:49.180
You may not understand those
rules, but there are rules.

00:53:49.180 --> 00:53:51.480
And I wouldn't worry
about that so much.

00:53:51.480 --> 00:53:55.030
I'd worry more about making sure
that those communities,

00:53:55.030 --> 00:53:57.050
those people, have
a stake in the

00:53:57.050 --> 00:53:58.890
society, the larger society.

00:53:58.890 --> 00:54:01.490
And one way you do that is
make sure they have jobs.

00:54:01.490 --> 00:54:04.560
Make sure that they have
potential opportunities to

00:54:04.560 --> 00:54:06.600
contribute to the
larger society.

00:54:06.600 --> 00:54:09.220
Make sure they're not
socially isolated.

00:54:09.220 --> 00:54:13.120
All of those are far more
important than us worrying

00:54:13.120 --> 00:54:14.430
about whether they have rules.

00:54:14.430 --> 00:54:17.370
And one of the things that
concerns me most of all is

00:54:17.370 --> 00:54:21.960
when I give this presentation
to certain groups, they say

00:54:21.960 --> 00:54:25.440
that they are concerned about
those communities, but that

00:54:25.440 --> 00:54:27.490
concern is disingenuous.

00:54:27.490 --> 00:54:30.900
Because their only concern when
someone like me comes

00:54:30.900 --> 00:54:32.380
along and say, hey,
we need to do

00:54:32.380 --> 00:54:35.590
something radically different.

00:54:35.590 --> 00:54:37.460
But when you look at--

00:54:37.460 --> 00:54:38.370
have you gone?

00:54:38.370 --> 00:54:39.340
Have you said anything?

00:54:39.340 --> 00:54:40.390
Have you contributed?

00:54:40.390 --> 00:54:42.650
Have you tried to change
the situation in those

00:54:42.650 --> 00:54:43.540
communities?

00:54:43.540 --> 00:54:45.020
No.

00:54:45.020 --> 00:54:50.120
And so, I think that the things
that I outlined--

00:54:50.120 --> 00:54:52.150
skills, jobs, all those--

00:54:52.150 --> 00:54:53.400
are far more important.

